      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(mcp): serialize OAuth refresh tokens",
        "body": "## Summary\n- serialize rotating MCP OAuth refresh-token use with a per-store lock\n- avoid replaying stale refresh tokens by returning newly persisted tokens when another process already refreshed\n- persist OAuth token metadata atomically with obtained/expires timestamps and terminal invalid_grant state\n\n## Context\nNotion MCP refresh tokens rotate on every refresh; concurrent refreshes can replay a stale token and invalidate the grant. This hardens the generic OpenClaw MCP OAuth provider for that class of MCP server.\n\n## Verification\n- npm test -- --run src/agents/mcp-oauth.test.ts src/agents/mcp-transport.test.ts\n- npm run tsgo:core\n- git diff --check",
        "branch": "fix/mcp-oauth-refresh-serialization",
